body:
Hmm....the error about CAMetalLayer seems to be gone with the most recent master branch build of GLFW and the latest version of the VulkanSDK and Mojave.

Still `glfwCreateWindowSurface` returns error: `Vulkan: Loader not found`

Seems the way GLFW loads the Vulkan lib is different than we do it in our engine:

GLFW:
```c
#if defined(_GLFW_VULKAN_LIBRARY)
    _glfw.vk.handle = _glfw_dlopen(_GLFW_VULKAN_LIBRARY);
#elif defined(_GLFW_WIN32)
    _glfw.vk.handle = _glfw_dlopen("vulkan-1.dll");
#elif defined(_GLFW_COCOA)
    _glfw.vk.handle = _glfw_dlopen("libvulkan.1.dylib");
#else
    _glfw.vk.handle = _glfw_dlopen("libvulkan.so.1");
#endif`
```
VOLK Vulkan loader:
```c
        void* module = dlopen("libvulkan.dylib", RTLD_NOW | RTLD_LOCAL);
	if (!module)
		module = dlopen("libvulkan.dylib.1", RTLD_NOW | RTLD_LOCAL);
	if (!module)
		module = dlopen("libMoltenVK.dylib", RTLD_NOW | RTLD_LOCAL);
	if (!module)
		return VK_ERROR_INITIALIZATION_FAILED;`
```
